00:05:55,666 --> 00:05:58,958
but a fundamental shift in how you experience reality

125
00:05:59,541 --> 00:06:01,833
so now that we know what these moments feel like

126
00:06:01,833 --> 00:06:04,000
let's explore the freedom that comes

127
00:06:04,291 --> 00:06:06,750
when the prison of self begins to dissolve

128
00:06:11,833 --> 00:06:14,875
think about how much of your life is spent defending

129
00:06:14,875 --> 00:06:15,500
maintaining

130
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,791
and worrying about this self you think you are

131
00:06:18,541 --> 00:06:20,250
when someone criticizes you

132
00:06:20,250 --> 00:06:22,833
it hurts because they're attacking your self image

133
00:06:23,125 --> 00:06:25,125
when you compare yourself to others

